summary: An Ordinance repealing Ordinance No. 7913, entitled "An Ordinance providing for the improvement of Minor Avenue, in the City of Seattle, from Roy Street to Aloha Street; and Aloha Street, from Minor Avenue to Eastlake Avenue, by grading curbing and parking the same, in conformity with the plans, and providing for the payment therefor by the mode of "Payment by Bonds," as provided by an act of the Legislature of the State of Washington, entitled "An act authorizing the issuance and sale of bonds by cities, to pay for local improvements, providing for the payment thereof, and declaring an emergency," approved March 14, 1899, and Ordinance No. 5693 of said City, approved December 6, 1899.
